==English==
===Noun===
'''[[assigned]] [[servant]]'''
# {{AU}} In the days when Australia was a penal settlement: a [[convict]] assigned to work as a servant for a [[free settler]] (either a male or female convict, and either a male or female settler).
===Usage notes===
The term [[convict]] was considered an insult in early colonial Australia (reference: [[w:Robert Hughes|Robert Hughes]], ''The Fatal Shore'', 1987, paperback ISBN 1-86046-150-6, page xi.).  ''Assigned servant'' was one of several euphemisms; see [[convict]] for others.